Update to Ticket Purchases
Coy Holcombe <cholcombe@eustaceisd.net>

Dear Parents/Guardians,

I hope this email finds you safe and healthy. I have a couple of updates for you regarding the Middle School football games in Westwood and varsity football game in Westwood.

• Middle School Football Games on Thursday - Westwood has informed us that no pre-sales will be required for the Middle School football games. You will pay at the gate in Westwood.

• High School Varsity Football on Friday - You will pick up the ticket voucher from the Admin Building. You will pay at the gate in Westwood when you present your voucher.
On Friday, please remember that the ticket voucher only entitles you to buy a ticket at Westwood. You will be required to pay at the gate.

If you have any questions, please let me know.

Coy

All classrooms and learning areas on campus will continue to be sanitized and disinfected throughout the day. Precautions are being taken each and every day to ensure the health and safety of our students and staff. If you have any questions or concerns, please give us a call. Thank you.

Dear Parents/Guardians,

I hope this email finds you and your family safe and healthy. We will be doing our weekly meal distribution tomorrow. You may pick up meal bags at the High School from 9:00 AM until 11:00 AM. Also, I will be getting another letter to you about the start of school for the 2020-2021 school year later in the week.

As always, if you have any questions, please let me know. Also, if there is anything that we may do for you, please do not hesitate to ask.

Coy

Eustace High School Cafe
June 25 at 3:26 PM ·

I was talking to a parent the other day and I asked her had she applied for the P-EBT and she told me no because she knew already she would not be approved because of income . If your child attends a CEP district then your child is AUTOMATICALLY approved. Eustace ISD is a CEP district . EACH child in the household will receive $285.00 to be spent on food . All you have to do is fill out the application . The application is very simple and only takes only a couple minutes . The deadline is June 30th . I highly recommend that you take advantage of this. If you need any help or have any questions , please let me know .

Thank you ,

Carolyn Davis
Director of Foodservice
903-425-5119

Eustace Independent School District
June 24 at 7:43 PM ·

Dear Parents/Guardians,

I want to inform you that we have had a student test positive for the Covid-19 virus and that the student did participate in the summer workout program. Out of an overabundance of caution, we are suspending the summer workout program until Thursday, July 9, 2020. The suspension also includes the summer cross country workouts.

The district will make sure that all inside areas that were used in the summer workout program will be disinfected beyond what is normally done. Parents are urged to monitor their children for signs of the virus, such as coughing and fever.

I know that our students and coaches were enjoying the summer workout program. This is not an end to the program, just a two-week pause. If you have any questions, please let me know.

Coy Holcombe

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians,

I hope this email finds you safe and healthy. I want to remind everyone that we will be doing our meal pick up tomorrow at the High School starting at 9:00 AM and going until 11:00 AM. If you cannot make it to the High School, we will be glad to bring the meals to your home. All I need is your address and the number of meal bags required.

Last week, I told you that TEA Commissioner Mike Morath would be giving us guidelines for this coming fall in his Tuesday webinar. He did not feel that he had all the necessary information for us and did not release any information. He has assured us that this Tuesday the information will be available. If he does provide information for the fall semester, I will send out an email on Wednesday.

If there is anything that we may do for you, please do not hesitate to contact us.

Also, I forgot to mention that the Meals to You Program has been extended to August 15, 2020. This is a much longer timeline for the program than last year.

Coy

Dear Parents/Guardians,

I hope this email finds you safe and healthy. We will be doing our meal distribution tomorrow at the High School from 9:00 AM until 11:00 AM. I know that some of you that are receiving the Meals to You boxes have gotten boxes that are damaged and had the contents ruined. I am sorry that this has happened and encourage you to continue to let us know about any problems you may experience. If you cannot make it to the High School tomorrow, we will be happy to deliver the meals to your home. All I need is your address and the number of meal bags that you need.

We are supposed to hear some news about the fall semester from the commissioner on Tuesday. If we learn of definite information on Tuesday, I will pass that on to everyone.

I want to again thank you for your patience and cooperation over the last several months.

Dear Parents/Guardians,

I hope this email finds you safe and healthy. I want to share some information regarding physicals for students involved in extracurricular activities for the 2020-2021 school year.

We will be hosting physicals this Friday, June 12th in the Kirk Gym for anyone who needs them. Physicals will begin at 8:00 AM and last until 12:00 PM. They will cost $10 per student. Please enter in through the foyer doors in the front of the Kirk Gym.

All incoming 7th graders that are going to participate in any sport(this includes cheerleading) will need a physical.

All incoming 9th grade band students will need a physical.

We are encouraging all athletes(this includes cheerleading), regardless of grade level, to take advantage of the very low cost and update their physical.

If you have any questions, please contact our head athletic trainer, Ashley Coker, at acoker@eustaceisd.net.

Thanks,

Coy Holcombe

Email from the Superintendent

Dear Parents/Guardians,

I hope this email finds you safe and healthy. We will be doing our meal pick up tomorrow. The High School site will be open from 9:00 AM until 11:00 AM. The remote sites will be available from 9:30 AM until 10:30 AM.

If you cannot make it to the High School or one of the remote sites, we will be glad to deliver the meals to your home. All I need is your address and the number of meal bags.

A reminder that the baccalaureate service and graduation ceremony have been moved. The baccalaureate service will be Wednesday, May 27 at 8:00 PM at Bulldog Stadium. The graduation ceremony will be Saturday, May 30 at 9:00 AM. These moves were necessary because of the regional bass tournament being on June 6.

Again, I thank you for your patience, understanding, and cooperation in all of this.

If you need anything, or we may do anything for you, please do not hesitate to let us know.

Coy Holcombe

cholcombe@eustaceisd.net

Dear Parents/Guardians,

I hope this email finds you and your family safe and healthy. I want to remind everyone that we will be doing a meal pick up tomorrow. You may pick up meals at the High School from 9:00 AM until 11:00 AM. You may pick up meals at our remote sites from 9:30 AM until 10:30 AM. Even if you are receiving the meal boxes, you may still pick up meals from the school. If you need your meals delivered to you, please email me with your address and the number of meal bags needed.

If you have questions about your child's assignments, please let me know or email the campus principal.

A reminder that if you have not signed up for the Summer Meals to You Program, the deadline has been extended to May 8th. Here is the link to sign up for the Summer Program: -- https://mealstoyou.org/meals-to-you-texas/

If there is anything that we may do for you, or if you have any questions, please do not hesitate to ask.

Coy Holcombe

post_text:
Email from the Superintendent - cholcombe@eustaceisd.net

Dear Parents/Guardians,

I hope this email finds you safe and healthy. We have just received word that the Summer Meals to You Program is still taking applications and will continue to take applications through midnight on May 8th. If you did not sign up during our first window, please take time to complete the online application at https://mealstoyou.org/meals-to-you-texas/ .

If you do not have a way to complete the application online, please let us know and we will make arrangements to help you get enrolled in the program.

As a reminder, the Emergency Meals to You Program is what is in place right now. You will continue to receive these boxes through June 30, 2020. The Summer Program is a different program that will provide meals during the summer break from school. These meals will probably start the first of July.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to let me know.

Coy Holcombe

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians,

First, I want to thank everyone for their patience and cooperation with yesterday's meal pick up. A total of 1,096 meal bags were picked up.

Second, I want to update you about the school closure. At this time, we have not received word that Governor Abbott will extend the closure; however, I do not believe that we are in a position to even think about opening schools up again. With that, Eustace ISD will remain closed until further notice. I believe that this is the only decision possible to ensure that our students, staff, and community remain healthy.

EISD will continue to provide meals and instructional support for our students throughout the closure. I know that there will be challenges for families because of the extended closure. Please let us know if there is anything we can do to help.

Again, I thank you for your patience and understanding in this ever changing situation.

Coy Holcombe
Superintendent
Eustace ISD

shared_text:
Eustace Middle School
March 29 at 10:13 PM ·

EMS Students and Guardians,

We will be passing out devices and packets tomorrow (3/30) from 9-11 am. We will be set up under the awning in the bus loop. Please follow the signs, as we have it set-up so you will pull around the bus loop with your driver side door towards the awning. Please do not get out of your car for any reason. All devices and packets have been disinfected and packaged up for your safety. We will be wearing gloves and masks also for your safety. More than likely it will be raining, but that will not stop us.

This is not a time to request a device or packet, all requests must go through your student’s homeroom teacher and we will contact you to set up a time to help you.

Due to meal count numbers, please plan on picking up your weekly meal boxes from your normal locations.

Please be patient as we will get them out to you as quickly as possible.

Thanks,

Michael Rowland
Principal
Eustace Middle School

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians,

We have received the email with the link to sign up for the summer meal program. **This program has nothing to do with what we are currently doing for our students**. The Summer Meals to You program is what we participated in last summer where the boxes of food arrived every week at your home. Since we participate in the Community Eligibility Provision, all of our students are eligible to participate in the Summer Meals to You program.

The website for Eustace families to sign up for Meals to You is here https://mealstoyou.org/meals-to-you-texas/ . **The registration for Eustace ISD students is from March 27 - April 6**. I encourage you to sign up to participate in this program. Because of the great success of this program last year and because of the expansion of this program to other districts, I am unsure at this time if everyone who signs up will actually receive these meals; however, please do not let that keep you from signing up.

If you have any questions, please let me know.

Coy Holcombe

shared_text:
Eustace High School
March 22 at 7:51 PM ·

Good afternoon parents and students! As you know, we were originally scheduled to begin school tomorrow and Governor Abbott has closed schools through at least April 3rd. This, however, does not mean that we will not be providing students with instruction.

As we will have to completely redesign our instructional methods, the state has insisted that we take time to plan appropriately. We will be taking time this week to do just that. As soon as we have a well-articulated plan, we will communicate it to you. We anticipate being able to do so by the end of the week.

Thank you for your patience while we work to continue providing a world-class education to our students!

March 23 at 12:09 AM ·

Dear Parents & Guardians,

I know that there are many questions and concerns regarding COVID-19 and the closure of our school. With our Spring Break coming to a close, we will be spending this next week making and finalizing plans to introduce our distance learning platforms. Please be patient with us as we work hard to put plans in place that will serve everyone's needs. We will be sending out a survey to gather information so we can tailor instruction as much as possible. If you have any questions or concerns in the meantime, please email your child's teacher or myself at jgray@eustaceisd.net. We will do our best in answering your questions and addressing your concerns. Thank you for your support as we all learn through this process together.

Sincerely,

Julie Gray
Principal

Dear Parents & Guardians,

I know that there are many questions and concerns regarding COVID-19 and the closure of our school. With our Spring Break coming to a close, we will be spending this next week making and finalizing plans to introduce our distance learning platforms. Please be patient with us as we work hard to put plans in place that will serve everyone's needs. We will be sending out a survey to gather information so we can tailor instruction as much as possible. If you have any questions or concerns in the meantime, please email your child's teacher or myself at jgray@eustaceisd.net. We will do our best in answering your questions and addressing your concerns. Thank you for your support as we all learn through this process together.

Sincerely,

Julie Gray
Principal

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians,

Governor Abbott has issued an order closing all schools in the state until at least April 3rd. All EISD facilities will be closed for any purpose until we get the clearance to resume.

We also received an email from UIL that states that the earliest any type of UIL activity could resume is Monday, May 4.

Our administrative team and food service team will be meeting today to determine the best way to get food to our students within the guidelines allowed.
We will also be talking about remote learning possibilities for our students.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact me.

Coy Holcombe

Eustace High School Senior and Theater Arts Student, Trey Oakley performed two acting monologues for about 30 colleges and Universities in the State of Texas at the Texas Educational Theatre Association workshops and student auditions today. Out of around 30 schools, he received callbacks from 13 interested schools for scholarship opportunities and acceptance into their Theater Programs.

He received callbacks from the following:

University of Texas- El Paso

University of Texas- Arlington

East Texas Baptist University

University of Southern Indiana

Midwestern State University

Sarofim School of Fine Arts- Southwestern University

Texas Wesleyan University

College of the Mainland

Baylor University

Lee College

Texas Lutheran College

AMDA

U.I.W.

Trey will finish up the second half of the audition process on Sunday by interviewing with each of the colleges about their offered programs.

Congratulations Trey! Bulldog Proud!

Dear Parents/Guardians,

I hope your summer break has started well. I wanted to remind you that our Summer Feeding Program is starting today and goes through June 27. Meals will be served Monday through Thursday. Anyone 18 years of age or younger may eat breakfast and lunch at no cost. There are no forms required. Breakfast will be served from 7:30 - 8:30 and lunch will be served from 11:30-12:30. All the meals will be served in the High School cafeteria.

Also, I wanted to let you know that the registration deadline has been extended on the Meals to You program. All students enrolled in Eustace ISD can receive meals delivered to their homes this summer! Sign up today at https://bit.ly/2wuigby or learn more at mealstoyou.org.

If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to ask.

Sincerely,

Coy Holcombe
Superintendent

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians,
First, I want to thank everyone for their thoughts and comments about changing this Friday from an early out day to an all day holiday. I appreciate you taking the time to respond. After reading all of the responses, I can tell you that the overwhelming choice was to change Friday to a holiday. So, this will serve as the official announcement that Friday will go from an early release day to a school holiday. Thursday, March 7, will be a regular school day. It will not be an early out day.
Again, thank for your responses. I hope everyone has a safe, enjoyable, and relaxing spring break!
Coy Holcombe
Superintendent

Again, thank for your responses. I hope everyone has a safe, enjoyable, and relaxing spring break!
Coy Holcombe

shared_text:
Eustace Intermediate School
March 19, 2018 at 2:18 PM ·

Many of you know Kooper. He is a 5th grader here at the Intermediate School. Kooper has been diagnosed with Periventricular Leukomalacia (PVL) with a second and third diagnosis of Cerebral Palsy and mild to moderate developmental delay. As a child with PVL gets older, seizures are usually part of the deal. While he has had several Grand Mal Seizures, he primarily suffers from silent seizures. Beginning today, Monday, March 19th through Friday, March 30th the Intermediate School will be hosting a penny drive, Pennies for Kooper and Kash, to donate to the fund to help provide training for Kash to become a service dog for Kooper. We are asking students to give what they can for the next two weeks, whether it is a little or a lot, so that we do our best to help Kooper and Kash!

post_text:
Dear Parents/Guardians,
Over the past few days, we have been carefully monitoring the number of absences throughout the district. While we thought we were seeing some improvement at the middle of this week, that improvement did not last. Today, we have 163 students absent. This does not include the ones that have been sent home today for not feeling well. We are also seeing an increasing number of staff members that are coming down with flu-like symptoms. As a result, we are going to take advantage of the three day weekend that was already scheduled and turn it into a four day weekend by canceling all classes for Friday, January 12.
We have GermBlast schedule to be here on Monday. They will be providing treatments to all the buildings in the district, as well as our buses. I apologize for any inconvenience this cancellation may cause. I feel this to be in the best interest of our students and staff.

Coy Holcombe
Superintendent

This Week | The Yard

Eustace Independent School District
October 2, 2017 at 9:19 PM ·

This WeekCoy Holcombe

Congratulations to the varsity volleyball team on closing out the first half of district play with a 3-1 win over Edgewood! The Lady Bulldogs start the second half of district this Tuesday when they host Mineola. First game is set to start at 4:30.

The Bulldogs lost a hard fought district game against Groesbeck, 20-19. The Bulldogs will host Teague this Friday. Kickoff is set for 7:30.

This Week

Monday – Middle School Volleyball -5:00 PM – Eustace; Band Practice – 6:30

Tuesday – JV & V District Volleyball v. Mineola – 4:30

Wednesday – Intermediate School – Fund Raiser Begins

Thursday – MS Football at Malakoff – 5:00; JV District Football at Teague – 6:00

Friday – JV & V District Volleyball v. Grand Saline – 4:30; Varsity District Football v. Teague – 7:30

Saturday – Mesquite Marching Festival

Monday, October 9 – District Holiday; District Cross Country Meet at Mineola

I hope everyone has a great week!

post_text:
FAFSA for Seniors; Career/Interest Inventory websites

October 1 was the first day the FAFSA (Free Application for Federal Student Aid) application for the 2018-19 school year to be open. Seniors who plan to attend college or any vocational education program need to fill this out to get any federal or state grants, or any financial aid from prospective schools. Visit www.fafsa.gov to get detailed information and to access the application. To get the most benefits available, fill out this application as soon as possible.

Students are invited to visit texascareercheck.com or texasoncourse.org for interest inventories and career information.

Board Meeting Last NightCoy Holcombe

Last night, the Eustace ISD Board of Trustees held their regular monthly meeting. The Board took the following actions:

Approved the minutes of previous meetings.

Approved the financial reports as presented.

Approved the Resolution to Offer Struck-Off Properties at Sheriff’s Tax Foreclosure Sale as amended.

Approved the 2017-2018 District Improvement Plan.

Approved the 2017-2018 Campus Improvement Plans.

Approved the purchase of up to 4 flat panel interactive screens.

Accepted the resignation of Misty Chestnut.

Approved the employment of Norma Rueter, cook at the High School; Eric McLeod, custodian at the Middle School; Tiffany Smith, PPCD aide at the Primary; Shelby Stegent, 1st grade teacher.

Approved the substitute list as presented.

Approved the student transfers as presented.

Adjourned.

post_text:
Family Access – Food Service AlertsCoy Holcombe
For parents of High School students, you may easily set up an email notification when your child’s food service balance falls below $5.00. After you log into Family Access, look at the top of the page for the link My Account. Click on the My Account link. It open a new page. Scroll down to the bottom of the page. You will see a section called Email Notifications. You have the option of checking a box to receive email notifications for grade alerts and email notifications when your child’s food service balance drops below $5.00. You can choose to receive both types of notifications or just the food service notifications.

I have used this option for several years. It is a great way for parents to know when they need to send more money for meals.

Note: Parents of students in grades PK – 8 do not need to bother with the food service notifications because all students in those grades eat at no cost.

shared_text:
PRESS.EUSTACEISD.NET
Google Password Resets

Eustace Independent School District
July 12, 2017 at 8:41 PM ·

Google Password Resets
Some high school students in upper grades may suddenly be unable to login to their district Google account if they are not using the “default” password we routinely assign them. If you hear of a student having this problem please let them know their password is their 2-digit class/grad-year followed by their 6-digit student ID/lunch number.

Recent account maintenance included resetting passwords; however, students in lower grades and campuses should not have a problem, since they cannot change them from default.

Please call or refer them to me if there are still problems or questions.

Rusty Meyners
Eustace ISD Technology
903 425 5137

post_text:
Summer School and Summer Feeding ProgramCoy Holcombe
Summer school starts Monday, June 5 and will end Thursday, June 29. If you have any questions about summer school, please contact the campuses.

Eustace ISD will again be hosting the Summer Feeding Program. Anyone who is 18 years of age or younger may participate in this program at no cost. There is no paperwork required. EISD will be hosting the Summer Program in the High School cafeteria. Breakfast is from 7:30 – 8:30. Lunch is served from 11:30 – 12:30. I encourage you to take full advantage of this program. Your child does NOT have to be in summer school in order to participate!

If you have any questions about the Summer Feeding Program, you may contact Rosemary Abbott at rabbott@eustaceisd.net, or you may send me an email at cholcombe@eustaceisd.net.

post_text: Neighbors helping neighbors!
shared_text:
Van ISD is with Tiffany Dunn and 4 others.
May 24, 2017 at 4:15 PM ·

Our last stop on the Kona Ice Snow Cone Tour with Justin Hargrove and Greg & Lee Ann Hammond was at Eustace Independent School District and Rains ISD! It was another great day full of smiles and snow cones with Vince and the girls! Thank you Justin, Greg, and Lee Ann for generously donating all the snow cones! #WeAreVan #ETXStrong #SmilesAndSnowCones #KonaIce with - Blair Camp, Elizabeth Harvey
